### Terminal UI Patterns

The CLI uses **no third-party UI libraries**. All user-facing patterns are:

#### Output Pattern (used in every command)

```typescript
const write = (msg: string) => process.stdout.write(`${msg}\n`);
const writeError = (msg: string) => process.stderr.write(`${msg}\n`);
```

This pattern appears in:
- `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/medan/apps/cli/src/commands/upload.ts:28-33`
- `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/medan/apps/cli/src/commands/login.ts:13-14`
- `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/medan/apps/cli/src/commands/logout.ts:5`
- `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/medan/apps/cli/src/commands/whoami.ts:5-6`
- `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/medan/apps/cli/src/commands/enable.ts:28-29`
- `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/medan/apps/cli/src/commands/set-org.ts:23-24`
- `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/medan/apps/cli/src/commands/disable.ts:9`

#### Interactive Prompt Pattern (readline-based)

A `promptChoice` function exists in two places with identical implementation:

- `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/medan/apps/cli/src/commands/enable.ts:12-25`
- `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/medan/apps/cli/src/commands/set-org.ts:7-20`

Both use `createInterface` from `node:readline`:
```typescript
async function promptChoice(question: string, max: number): Promise<number> {
	const rl = createInterface({ input: process.stdin, output: process.stdout });
	return new Promise((resolve) => {
		rl.question(question, (answer) => {
			rl.close();
			const num = Number.parseInt(answer.trim(), 10);
			if (Number.isNaN(num) || num < 1 || num > max) {
				resolve(1);
			} else {
				resolve(num);
			}
		});
	});
}
```

This is used for numbered-list selection of organizations. The pattern prints a list like:
```
  1. OrgName (slug)
  2. OrgName2 (slug2)
Choice [1-2]:
```
If input is invalid, it defaults to choice `1`.

#### Error Handling Pattern

All commands use `process.exitCode = 1` followed by `return` (never `process.exit(1)`). Errors go to `process.stderr`. This pattern is consistent across:
- `upload.ts:39`, `upload.ts:52`, `upload.ts:66`, `upload.ts:143`
- `login.ts:98`
- `whoami.ts:27`
- `enable.ts:34`, `enable.ts:44`, `enable.ts:52`
- `set-org.ts:29`, `set-org.ts:39`, `set-org.ts:45`

#### No Colors, No Spinners

There are no ANSI escape codes, no colored output, no progress spinners, and no animated terminal output anywhere in the CLI codebase. All messages are plain text strings.

